      "slug": "neo-noir",
      "title": "Neo-Noir",
      "desc": "Neo-noir is a style often seen in modern motion pictures and other forms that prominently use elements of film noir, but with updated themes, content, style, visual elements or media that were absent in film noir of the 1940s and 1950s.",
      "owner": "List by Snake Plissken",
      "tags": []
    },
    {
      "href": "/saithkar/list/neo-noir/",
      "user": "saithkar",
      "slug": "neo-noir",
      "title": "Neo Noir",
      "desc": "Neo noir is difficult to pin down, it's broadly post-1960 films that use film noir tropes – flawed antiheroes, femme fatales, moral ambiguity, urban settings, high-contrast lighting, plots involving murder and betrayal etc. – but in a modern or even fantastical setting, but can also apply to movies that deconstruct some of these tropes. A lot of time there is overlap with other genres such as action, crime and science fiction, but at a minimum there must be a commitment to a striking visual style and the story should focus on the dark side of human nature.",
      "owner": "List by Nick Langdon PATRON",
      "tags": []
    },
